    <div class="lang-block" data-lang="en" style="display:none">

      <h2>§ 1 Contracting Parties</h2>
      <p>
        This rental agreement is concluded between:<br>
        <strong>Operator:</strong> Nero Lefkada Rental&Retail, represented by managing director Kristina Goldberg, Lygia Port, 311 00 Lefkada, Greece · WhatsApp: +30 695 561 2777<br>
        <strong>Renter:</strong> The person making a booking and signing the safety briefing form.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 2 Subject Matter</h2>
      <p>
        The operator provides the renter with a personal watercraft (jetski) for recreational use on the Ionian Sea off Lefkada for a limited time period. The rental is subject to the following conditions and in compliance with Greek Law 4926/2022 and Presidential Decree 23/2000.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 3 Booking & Payment</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Bookings are confirmed upon payment of a <strong>30% deposit</strong> of the total price.</li>
        <li>The remaining balance is due on the day of rental before departure.</li>
        <li>Accepted payment methods: Viva Wallet, cash (EUR), credit/debit card.</li>
        <li><strong>Minimum age:</strong> 18 years. Valid photo ID must be presented on site.</li>
        <li><strong>Boating licence:</strong> Renters <strong>without</strong> a boating licence may only operate the jet ski as part of a guided tour with a Nero Lefkada guide. Renters <strong>with</strong> a valid EU boating licence (personal-watercraft category) may operate solo within the permitted zone and rules.</li>
        <li>Meeting point: Lygia Port, Lefkada. GPS coordinates are provided with booking confirmation.</li>
        <li>Operating hours: Monday to Sunday, 09:00–21:00, May to October.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>§ 3a No right of withdrawal for water-sports rentals</h2>
      <p>
        Under <strong>Article 16(l) of Directive 2011/83/EU (EU Consumer Rights Directive)</strong>, implemented in Greek law by <strong>Article 3κβ of Law 2251/1994</strong>, rentals of watercraft for a specific date or period are <strong>exempt from the statutory 14-day right of withdrawal</strong>. After booking confirmation, only the cancellation terms in §4 apply. Weather-based cancellation by the Operator (Beaufort 5+) is unaffected — in that case you receive a full 100% refund or a free rebooking.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 4 Cancellation Policy</h2>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Notice given</th><th>Refund</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>More than 48 hours before departure</td><td>100% – full refund</td></tr>
          <tr><td>24 to 48 hours before departure</td><td>50% refund</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Less than 24 hours</td><td>No refund</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Weather cancellation by operator (Beaufort 5+)</td><td>100% refund or free rebooking</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>§ 5 Weather & Operational Suspension</h2>
      <p>
        In accordance with Greek Coast Guard regulations (P.D. 23/2000), operations are suspended when wind speeds reach Beaufort 5 or when weather conditions are otherwise deemed unsafe. The decision is made at the operator's discretion. Customers are notified immediately via WhatsApp. In the event of a weather cancellation by the operator, the renter is entitled to a full refund or free rebooking.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 6 Safety Rules</h2>
      <p>The following safety rules are mandatory and based on Greek law:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Safety briefing:</strong> All operators must complete a mandatory 10-minute safety briefing and confirm with a signature before departure. <span class="law-ref">(Law 4926/2022)</span></li>
        <li><strong>Life vest:</strong> Wearing a life vest is mandatory for all operators and passengers at all times. Vests are provided.</li>
        <li><strong>Maximum distance from shore:</strong> 700 metres. <span class="law-ref">(P.D. 23/2000)</span></li>
        <li><strong>Swimming zones:</strong> Entry into buoy-marked swimming zones is strictly prohibited. <span class="law-ref">(P.D. 23/2000)</span></li>
        <li><strong>Zero alcohol/drugs:</strong> Operating under the influence of alcohol or drugs is prohibited by Greek law and results in immediate termination without refund.</li>
        <li><strong>Authorised operator only:</strong> Only the person who signed the briefing may operate the watercraft.</li>
        <li><strong>Passenger capacity:</strong> Maximum 1 passenger on 2-seat models; maximum 2 passengers on 3-seat models.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>§ 7 Renter's Obligations</h2>
      <p>The renter agrees to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Treat the watercraft with the care of a responsible renter.</li>
        <li>Return the watercraft in its original condition.</li>
        <li>Report any damage immediately and in full.</li>
        <li>Comply with all applicable Greek Coast Guard and Lefkada Harbour Master regulations.</li>
        <li>Not transfer the watercraft to any third party.</li>
        <li>Not carry any items or substances prohibited under Greek law.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>§ 8 Prohibited Conduct</h2>
      <p>The following are expressly prohibited:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Stunts, flips or dangerous manoeuvres of any kind</li>
        <li>Exceeding the 700-metre coastal limit</li>
        <li>Entering harbour or shipping lanes other than the designated dock</li>
        <li>Approaching other vessels within 50 metres</li>
        <li>Entering swimming zones or approaching swimmers</li>
        <li>Consuming alcohol or drugs during the rental period</li>
        <li>Carrying more passengers than the seating capacity allows</li>
        <li>Intentional or grossly negligent damage to the watercraft</li>
        <li>Transferring the watercraft to an unauthorised operator</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>§ 9 Liability & Insurance</h2>

      <h3>9.1 Third-Party Liability Insurance</h3>
      <p>
        The watercraft is covered by mandatory third-party liability insurance of up to <strong>€700,000 per incident</strong>. <span class="law-ref">(Law 4926/2022, P.D. 284/1994)</span>
      </p>

      <h3>9.2 No Personal Accident Insurance for Operator / Passengers</h3>
      <div class="warn">
        <strong>Important:</strong> The watercraft's insurance does <strong>not</strong> cover personal injury to the operator or passengers. We strongly recommend taking out travel or sports insurance that includes water sports activities.
      </div>

      <h3>9.3 Security Deposit</h3>
      <p>
        A damage-free deposit may be required. The amount depends on the booked model and will be communicated during the booking process. The deposit is fully refunded provided the watercraft is returned undamaged.
      </p>

      <h3>9.4 Renter's Liability for Damage to Watercraft</h3>
      <p>
        Damage to the watercraft caused by the renter's gross negligence or intentional conduct is fully the renter's responsibility. Damage resulting from normal operation or unforeseeable events is excluded.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 10 Disclaimer of Liability</h2>

      <h3>10.1 Exclusion of Operator's Liability</h3>
      <p>The operator is not liable for personal injury, property damage or financial loss suffered by the renter, passengers or third parties arising from:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Non-compliance with these Terms or safety rules</li>
        <li>Gross negligence or intentional misconduct by the renter</li>
